  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">New Community-Informed Approaches to Humanitarian Protection and Restraint</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will work in the Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC). This research aims to provide new understandings and tools to both communities and humanitarian workers to reinforce protective measures. By identifying where such local protection measures have worked, and under what
circumstances, the research will provide an evidence base for policy and practice.</narrative>
